{"title":"Moving from Seattle to Austin: Complete Relocation Guide [2026]","description":"Compare cost of living, housing, taxes, and quality of life when moving from Seattle to Austin. Data-driven relocation guide with calculators.","url":"https://urcity.com/compare/moving-from-seattle-to-austin/","content":"\u003ch2 id=\"introduction\"\u003eIntroduction\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSeattle and Austin are two of America\u0026rsquo;s top tech hubs — but Austin offers dramatically lower costs while maintaining a robust tech scene. If you\u0026rsquo;re tired of Seattle\u0026rsquo;s housing prices and rainy winters, Austin might be your answer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"cost-of-living-comparison\"\u003eCost of Living Comparison\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eCategory\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSeattle\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSavings\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eOverall Index\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e172.1\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e119.3\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-31%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eRent (1BR)\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$2,350/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$1,650/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-$700/mo\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHome Price\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$820,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$450,000\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e-45%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eUtilities\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$130/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$140/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e+8%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eGroceries\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$520/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$380/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-27%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eTransportation\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$170/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$150/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-12%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eHealthcare\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$400/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e$350/mo\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e-13%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMonthly savings potential: $1,200–$2,000\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"salary-calculator\"\u003eSalary Calculator\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you make \u003cstrong\u003e$120,000 in Seattle\u003c/strong\u003e, you need approximately \u003cstrong\u003e$83,000 in Austin\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"calculator-widget\" id=\"salary-calc\"\u003e\n  \u003ch3\u003eSalary Comparison Calculator\u003c/h3\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eCurrent Salary ($)\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cinput type=\"number\" id=\"current-salary\" value=\"120000\" min=\"0\" step=\"1000\"\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eFrom City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"from-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" \u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-row\"\u003e\n    \u003clabel\u003eTo City\u003c/label\u003e\n    \u003cselect id=\"to-city\"\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"austin-tx\" selected\u003eAustin\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"nyc\" \u003eNew York City\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"sf\" \u003eSan Francisco\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"la\" \u003eLos Angeles\u003c/option\u003e\n      \u003coption value=\"chicago\" \u003eChicago\u003c/option\u003e\n    \u003c/select\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cbutton class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"calculateSalary()\"\u003eCalculate\u003c/button\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"calc-result\" id=\"salary-result\" style=\"display:none;\"\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eYou need \u003cstrong id=\"needed-salary\"\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e in \u003cspan id=\"target-city-name\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e to maintain the same standard of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003cp id=\"salary-difference\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cscript\u003e\nfunction calculateSalary() {\n  const salary = parseFloat(document.getElementById('current-salary').value);\n  const fromCity = document.getElementById('from-city').value;\n  const toCity = document.getElementById('to-city').value;\n  \n  const colIndex = {\n    'nyc': 187.2,\n    'sf': 269.3,\n    'la': 173.3,\n    'chicago': 110.8,\n    'austin-tx': 119.3\n  };\n  \n  const cityNames = {\n    'nyc': 'New York City',\n    'sf': 'San Francisco',\n    'la': 'Los Angeles',\n    'chicago': 'Chicago',\n    'austin-tx': 'Austin'\n  };\n  \n  const neededSalary = Math.round(salary * (colIndex[toCity] / colIndex[fromCity]));\n  const diff = salary - neededSalary;\n  \n  document.getElementById('needed-salary').textContent = '$' + neededSalary.toLocaleString();\n  document.getElementById('target-city-name').textContent = cityNames[toCity];\n  \n  const diffEl = document.getElementById('salary-difference');\n  if (diff \u003e 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would save \u003cstrong\u003e$' + diff.toLocaleString() + '/year\u003c/strong\u003e by moving.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-positive';\n  } else if (diff \u003c 0) {\n    diffEl.innerHTML = 'You would need \u003cstrong\u003e$' + Math.abs(diff).toLocaleString() + '/year more\u003c/strong\u003e to maintain your lifestyle.';\n    diffEl.className = 'savings-negative';\n  } else {\n    diffEl.textContent = 'Cost of living is roughly the same.';\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById('salary-result').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"housing-market\"\u003eHousing Market\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"seattle\"\u003eSeattle\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $820,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $2,350/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $520\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"austin\"\u003eAustin\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian home: $450,000\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedian rent (1BR): $1,650/month\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePrice per sq ft: $285\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAustin housing is 45% cheaper than Seattle.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"taxes\"\u003eTaxes\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eTax Type\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSeattle\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eState Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e0%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eCity Income Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e0%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e0%\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSales Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e10.25%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e8.25%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eProperty Tax\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~0.93%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e~1.8%\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBoth cities have no state income tax — a major advantage.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"climate\"\u003eClimate\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\t\u003cthead\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003e\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eSeattle\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cth\u003eAustin\u003c/th\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/thead\u003e\n\t\u003ctbody\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSummer High\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e76°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e96°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eWinter Low\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e37°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e41°F\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eSunny Days\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e152\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e228\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003ctr\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003eRainfall\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e37\u0026quot;\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ctd\u003e35\u0026quot;\u003c/td\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/tr\u003e\n\t\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrade-off:\u003c/strong\u003e Austin is much sunnier and hotter. Seattle has milder summers but gray winters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"culture--lifestyle\"\u003eCulture \u0026amp; Lifestyle\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-miss-from-seattle\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Miss from Seattle\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMountains and hiking (Rainier, Cascades)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoffee culture\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMild summer weather\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProgressive politics\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWater access (Puget Sound, lakes)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-youll-gain-in-austin\"\u003eWhat You\u0026rsquo;ll Gain in Austin\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e228 sunny days per year\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLive music capital of the world\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBBQ and Tex-Mex\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMore affordable everything\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo state income tax\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"best-neighborhoods-in-austin-for-seattle-transplants\"\u003eBest Neighborhoods in Austin for Seattle Transplants\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEast Austin\u003c/strong\u003e — Trendy, artsy, most like Capitol Hill\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSouth Congress\u003c/strong\u003e — Walkable shops and restaurants\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMueller\u003c/strong\u003e — Planned community with parks\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDowntown Austin\u003c/strong\u003e — Urban, like South Lake Union\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"is-it-worth-it\"\u003eIs It Worth It?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYes — if you prefer sun to rain.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth cities have no state income tax and strong tech economies. Austin is significantly cheaper (31% lower cost of living) and much sunnier. The main trade-offs are summer heat and less outdoor scenery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDisclaimer:\u003c/strong\u003e All cost of living figures, housing prices, tax estimates, and savings calculations on this page are provided for informational purposes only and do not constitute financial, legal, tax, or real estate advice. Actual costs and savings will vary based on your specific circumstances, lifestyle, income, deductions, and local market conditions. URCity and Northshore Press are not financial advisors, tax professionals, or real estate agents. Always consult qualified professionals before making relocation or financial decisions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"frequently-asked-questions\"\u003eFrequently Asked Questions\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"will-my-salary-go-down\"\u003eWill my salary go down?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePossibly.\u003c/strong\u003e Tech salaries in Austin are typically 10–20% lower than Seattle. However, the cost savings more than offset the difference.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"is-austins-tech-scene-as-good-as-seattles\"\u003eIs Austin\u0026rsquo;s tech scene as good as Seattle\u0026rsquo;s?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDifferent but robust.\u003c/strong\u003e Seattle has Microsoft and Amazon headquarters. Austin has Apple, Google, Meta, Tesla, Dell, and thousands of startups.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"whats-the-biggest-culture-shock\"\u003eWhat\u0026rsquo;s the biggest culture shock?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe heat and the driving.\u003c/strong\u003e Austin summers are extreme (100°F+). And unlike Seattle\u0026rsquo;s decent public transit, Austin is car-dependent.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"hows-the-outdoor-scene\"\u003eHow\u0026rsquo;s the outdoor scene?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGood but different.\u003c/strong\u003e Austin has Lady Bird Lake, Barton Springs, and Hill Country hiking. But it\u0026rsquo;s not the Pacific Northwest.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"data-sources\"\u003eData Sources\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCost of living: Council for Community and Economic Research (C2ER)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHousing data: Zillow Research\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTax data: Tax Foundation\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMigration data: IRS Statistics of Income\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eLast updated: June 28, 2026\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n"}